(Reuters) - The Biden administration released an executive order asking federal agencies to provide detailed reports on consumer safety and the parameters of a digital dollar. We talk with lawyers to get their take on the move and its significance. This video features commentary from Gary DeWaal, senior counsel with Katten Muchin Rosenman and Professor Carol Goforth of the University of Arkansas School of Law. Our Standards: The Thomson Reuters Trust Principles. Alex Cohen produces multimedia projects on legal trends, key cases, and industry issues. He can be reached at alex.cohen@thomsonreuters.com. You can follow him on Twitter @alexlcohen.